South Korea May Crude Oil Imports Rise 4.1 Percent by Volume

-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 
2011-06-01T03:01:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/south-korea-may-crude-oil-imports-rise-4-1-percent-by-volume-1-.html
South Korea ,  Asia ’s fourth-largest
crude-oil buyer, boosted May imports of the fuel by 4.1 percent
compared with a year earlier, the smallest increase since
October 2010, government data show.  Shipments rose to 79.2 million barrels from 76.1 million
barrels a year earlier, the  Ministry of Knowledge  Economy said
in an e-mailed statement today.  South Korea’s crude import bill gained 37 percent to $8.6
billion last month as Asian benchmark Dubai prices rose 41
percent to $108 a barrel, the ministry said.  Gas import costs increased 27 percent to $1.96 billion in
May, while coal prices climbed 66 percent to $1.47 billion,
according to the ministry.  Oil-product exports jumped 47 percent by value, while
shipments of petrochemicals rose 38 percent, the ministry said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangim Han in Seoul at 
 sihan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amit Prakash at 
 aprakash1@bloomberg.net . 